meta.description:
Betelguse - Alpha Ori (Star) 

Location:
Kuwait - Alhejen 

Description:  
The beautiful dying star betelguse! Situated at the shoulder of the orion constellation you can see this lovely star in a clear winter night. This star will soon go supernova and die and when that happens if we are alive will be a beautiful sight to see! The diffraction spikes are done by adding some wires to the telescope to diffract light. 

Equipment:
° Mount: Ioptron Cem40 with iPolar @ioptron_telescopes
° Main Imaging: ZWO ASI533MC Pro @zwoasi
° Filter: Optolong L-pro 1.25" @optolongfilter
° OTA: Skywatcher Esprit 100ED @skywatcherusa
° SW field flattener
° Guide Scope :  ZWO mini guide scope 120mm 
° Guide Camera: ZWO ASI-120MM-mini @zwoasi.
° Stellarmate - Wireless Astrophotography Controller @ikarustechnolog 

Integration: 
Lights: 40 x 60 seconds - gain 120
Darks: none
Flats:  20 x 0.2 seconds
Bias: none 

Total aquisition :  40 minutes 

Software:
Astro pixel processor 
Deep Sky Stacker
Adobe Photoshop 

Process: stacked in DSS, initial stretch in sequence and color calibration in astro pixel processor and finished up in photoshop, contrast and noise reduction.
